                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77 Chinese Eastern/493: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Perkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-11-29T21:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 29, 1929—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 29—10:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1058. Department’s [394,] November 28, noon. German Minister informs me that he
                    has as yet received no confirmation from either Berlin or Mukden of the report
                    that China has accepted Russian terms of settlement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
